    </StandardHierarchyLevel>
    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.6.NS.C.7c</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Understand the absolute value of a rational number as its distance from 0 on the number line; interpret absolute value as magnitude for a positive or negative quantity in a real-world situation. &lt;i&gt;For example, for an account balance of &amp;ndash;30 dollars, write |&amp;ndash;30| = 30 to describe the size of the debt in dollars&lt;/i&gt;.</Statement>
    </Statements>
